# F4 DUAL-RUN expected-divergence list (specs/v2.2-p6.5-dualrun.sh).
#
# The dual-run gate compares the FULL production path — `bin/ssc run P` (default front) vs
# `SSC_FRONT=F bin/ssc run P` (F) — capturing (exit, stdout). It is GREEN when every divergence is
# listed here; an UNEXPECTED divergence (F worse than the default front, not listed) is a genuine-FAIL.
#
# ★ SINCE THE F4a DELEGATE-FALLBACK (RunNativeV2), the UNBOUND-GLOBAL gap classes fall back cleanly:
# where F cannot lower a program it emits an unbound global, `Reader.validate` catches it, and RunNativeV2
# re-lowers the file through the default front → EQUAL. The residuals below are the class the fallback
# CANNOT catch: F resolves all globals but lowers a VALUE wrong, so the pre-check passes and F runs to a
# wrong result. On the DEFAULT slice: 43/43 EQUAL, 0 divergence.
#
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# COMPLETE FULL-CORPUS SWEEP — 2026-07-21 (SSC_DUALRUN_ALL=1, 521 programs, clean F-staged worktree).
#   Result: EQUAL 509/521, DIVERGE 12 = 2 expected-GAP + 10 real residuals + (http-client, scljet-sql-
#   orderby-expr were FALSE divergences — see NON-RESIDUAL section; excluded after per-program adjudication
#   default×1 + F×2 for determinism, timeout-group at 150s).
#   ALL 10 residuals are ONE class: F's MULTI-FILE (import) lowering emits wrong values. Single-file
#   programs are unaffected (that is why 509/521 are EQUAL). The flip stays BLOCKED on an F multi-file
#   lowering fix; the F4a fallback cannot catch these (globals resolve, values are wrong).
#   ⚠ 3 residuals are SILENT-WRONG (F exits 0 with wrong stdout): std-bifunctor, tagless-sealed-dispatch,
#     tkv2-theme-css-vars. Post-flip these would corrupt output with NO error — the strongest fix-first arg.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# format (TAB-separated):  <BUCKET>\t<program>\t<reason>
#   buckets: GAP (real F residual — needs multi-file lowering fix) / OUT / DEFERRED /
#            FLAKY (non-deterministic program, cannot byte-compare — NOT an F bug) /
#            SLOW  (F correct but slower than the sweep timeout — a FALSE timeout, NOT an F bug)
# NOTE: the gate's isGap() matches by program NAME in ANY bucket, so FLAKY/SLOW entries also suppress the
#   fail. A future REAL regression on a FLAKY/SLOW program would be masked — re-verify by hand if suspect.

# ── GAP — RUNTIME-CORRECTNESS residuals. MULTI-FILE programs where F's lowering of imported values is
#    WRONG while all globals resolve (static pre-check passes → F runs to a wrong result). NOT fallback-
#    catchable: a run-time rerun is unsafe (side-effect duplication; ~half the corpus is multi-file incl.
#    scljet DB writers). These need F's MULTI-FILE lowering fixed. Each verified DETERMINISTIC (F run twice,
#    identical) in a clean F-staged worktree on 2026-07-21. ──
GAP	dsl-ast-builder	multi-file (imports std/dsl/*.ssc): F lowers spanEmpty.start/end to a <closure>; default prints 0..0. Needs F multi-file lowering fix.
GAP	multi-link-imports	multi-file (imports std/money.ssc, std/either.ssc): F lowers a value to () → `no dispatch for .getOrElse on ()`, rc=1; default prints "minor units: 1234". Needs F multi-file lowering fix.
GAP	money-multisection	multi-file (imports std/money.ssc): F lowers a value to () → `__method__: no dispatch for .getOrElse on ()`, rc=1; default prints "zł~2~0~XXX~2". Same root cause as multi-link-imports. Needs F multi-file lowering fix.
GAP	money-portable-v2	multi-file (imports std/money.ssc): F lowers a value to () → `.getOrElse on ()`, rc=1; default prints "$3.75~true~1.2100~3.3333~1234~List(...)". Same root cause. Needs F multi-file lowering fix.
GAP	litdoc	multi-file (imports std/litdoc.ssc): F aborts with internal `ssc: 2`, rc=1, empty stdout; default prints 401 B ("kinds: front,heading,..."). Needs F multi-file lowering fix.
GAP	mcp-types	multi-file (imports std/mcp/types.ssc): F lowers a ctor with wrong arity → `arity: 2 expected, 1 given`, rc=1 after partial output (false/hello/true, 16 B); default prints full 107 B. Needs F multi-file lowering fix.
GAP	std-monaderror	multi-file (imports std/either.ssc, std/monaderror.ssc — typeclass givens): F aborts after partial output (None~Some(42)~None, 18 B), rc=1; default prints 192 B. Needs F multi-file/typeclass lowering fix.
GAP	std-bifunctor	SILENT-WRONG. multi-file (imports std/either.ssc, std/bifunctor.ssc — typeclass givens): F exits 0 but emits `Stub` for typeclass instances → wrong stdout (154 B vs default 183 B). No error. Needs F multi-file/typeclass lowering fix.
GAP	tagless-sealed-dispatch	SILENT-WRONG. multi-file (imports std/either.ssc, std/bifunctor.ssc, std/monaderror.ssc — typeclasses): F exits 0 but emits `Stub` → wrong stdout (69 B vs default 93 B). No error. Needs F multi-file/typeclass lowering fix.
GAP	tkv2-theme-css-vars	SILENT-WRONG. multi-file (imports std/ui/theme.ssc; NO typeclass): F exits 0 but computes wrong booleans (some true→false; 37 B vs default 34 B all-true). No error. Needs F multi-file lowering fix.

# ── NON-RESIDUALS — divergences the sweep flagged that are NOT F correctness bugs (adjudicated 2026-07-21;
#    listed so the full-corpus gate stays green, with the evidence to re-verify). ──
FLAKY	http-client	NETWORK non-determinism — the program's own output varies run-to-run (F1 rc=1 15 B vs F2 rc=1 0 B; default rc=124 timeout in the sweep vs rc=1 11 B on re-run). A non-deterministic program cannot be byte-compared; NOT an F bug.
SLOW	scljet-sql-orderby-expr	FALSE TIMEOUT — at DR_TIMEOUT≥150 F output is BYTE-IDENTICAL to default (sha ae1324ba, 335 B, verified twice). The sweep's 60s timeout was too short for F on this heavy scljet DB program (F rc=124). F is CORRECT here, just slower; NOT a residual. Raise DR_TIMEOUT for scljet in full sweeps.
